Following up on the success of 2008's Asuncion and 2010's Supermagique was no easy task for the Vancouver-based trio of vocalists that includes Silvana Kane, guitarist Adam Popowitz and bassist Toby Peter, so they took a new approach.
&quot;In the past the three of us would sit together and jam ideas,&quot; said Peter. &quot;This time Adam and I built a track, then Silvana could come in and vibe off of it.&quot;
Amor Planeta, which translates to &quot;love planet,&quot; is anchored in the familiar instrumentation that Pacifika is known for, but the band worked to incorporate more live performance and a little less electronica into the record. As a result, the record has a more lush, relaxed sound even in the more upbeat tracks like &quot;So Much Here&quot; or &quot;Bring It.&quot;
- Judith Lynch, CBC Music

